The Herald Marry Mubaiwa, the estranged wife of Vice President Chiwenga was on Monday morning formally placed on remand on the charge of attempting to kill her husband, the Vice President. Marry was remanded in custody to December 30 2019 for routine remand.<img class="aligncenter wp-image-463756 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/a617df4c-26b7-487e-9de7-0413a3635d03.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/a617df4c-26b7-487e-9de7-0413a3635d03.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/a617df4c-26b7-487e-9de7-0413a3635d03-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />The Harare regional court advised her to apply for bail at the High Court which has jurisdiction over such third schedule offences.
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-463759 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/95b19a51-f48e-473c-94a5-d26b112d6f85.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/95b19a51-f48e-473c-94a5-d26b112d6f85.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/95b19a51-f48e-473c-94a5-d26b112d6f85-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />Marry appeared in court facing the additional charge of attempting to kill her husband. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-463754 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/b825d5ae-e022-4341-82ed-45f19661387c.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/b825d5ae-e022-4341-82ed-45f19661387c.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/b825d5ae-e022-4341-82ed-45f19661387c-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />She was initially charged with externalization of US$1 million, fraudulently seeking to solemnise her marriage with neither the husband’s knowledge nor consent and money laundering.
